descript.abstract: The seventeen major drainage basins, or watersheds, which are the basis for management, monitoring, and assessment activities by the New York State Department of Environmental Conservation. The major basins are further divided into 68 (sub)basins.
descript.purpose: To identify major basins and (sub)basins that are the basis for management, monitoring, and assessment activities by the New York State Department of Environmental Conservation.
descript.supplinf: The Major Drainage Basins layer is based on the Watershed Boundary Dataset (WBD) 12 Digit HUC for New York State grouped according to the 17 major basins and their tribs (or contaminate basins depending on use). The WBD HUC12 data set was aquired by the NYS DEC Division of Water from the NRCS Data Gateway on 6/17/2011 (see Data Sources).
